title: For Sale:  Savage 10 Sniper Rifle 308
postcontent:
This is a gently used Savage 10 in 308 with the Choate Ultimate Sniper Stock. I've probably put about 150 rounds through it. I intend to sell it as I bought it, as a package. I believe the package was originally put together for law enforcement.

The package I'm selling includes:
- Savage 10 in .308
- bipod (specially made to fit this stock)
- oversized factory bolt knob
- matching gun case
- matching sling
- matching hearing protection
- cleaning kit
- log book with data on all my shots

The only piece you need is the scope. I have a Leupold Mark 4 LR/T 3.5-10x40mm (#60020) with TMR recticle. I'd be willing to include it for additional $$. I'll even include the mounts.

This has been an excellent rifle for me. Shoots sub MOA (about .6-.8 MOA I'd say) and I've hit silhouettes out to 1,100 yards with it (that's about as far as my skill can take it but the rifle might go farther). I'm only selling it to help pay for a custom $4k rifle I'm having built.

This would make an excellent starter rifle for someone just getting into long-range shooting. Savage 10s are known for incredible out of the box accuracy. The Savage AccuTrigger is also known as the best factory trigger with about 1/5-2lb trigger pull currently set. Not as nice as a aftermarket Timney or Jewell but those cost $250 a pop.

A word about the stock. The stock is packed full of features. It has a detachable monopod (I'm not a fan of monopods for field work but its excellent for benchrest shooting or zeroing the rifle), reenforced fore-end to keep the barrel truly free-floating, pistol-grip and rear hand-hold. The length of pull and comb height can be swapped out for different sizes to get the perfect fit.

Like I said its been a great rifle. Its been great for both plinking and hunting.

I will ship for free to an FFL. Email with any questions.

**UPDATE-- I've sold the other AK in under 24 hours!  Things are moving quickly!**

I have for sale a Saiga 7.62x39 AK.  These rifles are a stupendous variant of the AK species, with butter-smooth actions and excellent accuracy, without the sticker-shock you might get from an Arsenal.  Made in the Izhmash (now Kalashnikov Concern) company in Izhevsk, Russia, these are derived from the minds and machines who made the first AKs. Despite the embargo and panic, I'm keeping the price low on this one (don't mind the crazies charging $850 for these unconverted, damn opportunists, they are), as I bought it from a friend who needed cash fast for way less than the going value. This is in the unconverted style and takes proprietary Saiga magazines, the factory 10 rounder is included with this rifle.  If it was converted I'd price it closer to $900 (but you can do just that if you want after buying!).

Trigger breaks cleanly, and I swapped out the stock spring for a brass set to lighten trigger pull.  Barrel has 1/7 twist, so handles heavy projectiles and shoots 500 yards easily.  

I had started to make this my long range rifle, but started shooting shotgun.  Selling this to replenish the savings account after a recent purchase.  

$1200 buys the rifle, scope mount, Harris #5 swivel stud adapter, original springs and grip in addition to the brass springs and Hogue grip currently installed, 3 magazines (Colt 30-round, C products 30-round, Magpul 10-round), Caldwell brass catcher, and Plano case with foam cut to fit.  For an extra $150, I'll leave the Redfield Revenge 6-18x AO scope I currently have mounted.

I am happy to entertain a partial trade toward the purchase.  A couple ideas I would accept - SKS in excellent condition - nothing sporterized, just good wood with the 10 round box and bayonet still affixed.  S&W M&P Shield 40, Ruger GP101 or similar revolver in 357 Mag with a longer (6" preferred) barrel and adjustable sights, or another good carry piece.  I'm open to some options, but not multiple trade items, as my primary reason for selling the gun is to replenish the savings account.

If in the Roanoke region (within about an hour's drive), sale will be face to face and I will see your concealed carry permit or voter registration and drivers license.  A Bill of Sale is required. Thanks for looking!
